Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Grass-tree</i> ... (2) In New Zealand <i>Pseudopanax crassifolium</i>,  Seemann, <i>N.O. Araleaceae</i>. When young, this is the same as <i>Umbrella-tree</i>, so called from its appearance like the ribs of an umbrella. When older, it grows more straight and is called <i>Lancewood</i> (q.v.)....
